Biotin and avidin can specifically interact with their affinity (about 1015
 M−1
). Every avidin molecule has four interaction locations to be combined with biotin. When biotin is combined with high molecular weight, the biotin molecule can still be identified by the avidin. Using the method, oriented immobilization of bio-GP3 can be realized. We used the surface of silicon as a sensing surface to catch phage M13KO7, as described in references (Bisoffi et al., 2008, Qi et al., 2006b).
